OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F464A1773007876
OL,3,CWales win World Cup qualifier against
OL,4,CMontenegro with strong first-half show
OL,6,FHannah Cain and Mared Griffiths each
OL,7,Fscored twice as Wales claimed an
OL,8,Femphatic 6-1 World Cup qualifying
OL,9,Fvictory over Montenegro in Llanelli.
OL,11,FRhian Wilkinson's side were grateful
OL,12,Ffor a stoppage time equaliser from
OL,13,FElise Hughes in beginning their World
OL,14,FCup campaign with a 2-2 draw away to
OL,15,Fthe Czech Republic on Tuesday.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G1/6
